    <name>Use Know-Want-Learn (KWL) methods to reflect on learning goals​ ​</name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{92844aa9-8bbe-4831-8786-644c3a39d251}{44}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;A KWL chart is a great way to invite learners to reflect on their experience with goals and goal&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;setting. KWL refers to the key terms “know”, “want”, and “learn” in the following prompts:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul role="list"&gt;&lt;li data-aria-posinset="1" role="listitem" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{92844aa9-8bbe-4831-8786-644c3a39d251}{47}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-230,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;What I know about...&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-aria-posinset="2" role="listitem" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{92844aa9-8bbe-4831-8786-644c3a39d251}{50}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-230,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;What I want to know about...&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-aria-posinset="3" role="listitem" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{92844aa9-8bbe-4831-8786-644c3a39d251}{53}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-230,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;What I’ve learned...&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{92844aa9-8bbe-4831-8786-644c3a39d251}{56}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;The table below is an example of how to structure the KWL activity for goals. Ask learners to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;respond to the prompt about goals. Through this process learners have an opportunity to reframe&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;past accomplishments in terms of goals activating prior knowledge and relevance and help reduce&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;barriers to goal setting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;
